casebody.data:
Dayton Bar Association v. Ellison.

[Cite as Dayton Bar Assn. v. Ellison (1990), 50 Ohio St. 3d 131.]

(No. 89-2167 Submitted February 13, 1990 Decided April 11, 1990.) *132Charles Geidner, for relator. Kathy L. Ellison, pro se. Per Curiam.

We agree with the board’s findings of misconduct and its recommendation. Respondent is therefore publicly reprimanded for having violated DR 6-101(A)(3) and 7-101(A)(3). Costs taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
